  <section class="topic-landing__hero" aria-labelledby="topic-flourishing-heading">
    <div class="container topic-landing__hero-grid">
      <div class="topic-landing__hero-copy">
        <p class="topic-landing__eyebrow">Christian Transhumanist Association</p>
        <h1 id="topic-flourishing-heading">Technology and human flourishing</h1>
        <p class="topic-landing__lede">
          Powerful technology is changing work, bodies, communities, ecology, and culture. The question is not whether technology will shape the future, but whether it will be guided toward life, dignity, wisdom, and broad human flourishing.
        </p>
        <div class="topic-landing__actions">
          <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/join/future/">Join the conversation</a>
          <a class="btn btn-default btn-lg" href="#resources">Explore CTA resources</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="topic-landing__signal" aria-label="Core questions">
        <p class="topic-landing__signal-label">A practical framework</p>
        <ol>
          <li><span>Purpose</span> What human goods should this technology serve?</li>
          <li><span>Dignity</span> Who is protected as capabilities expand?</li>
          <li><span>Access</span> Who benefits, and who is left behind?</li>
          <li><span>Stewardship</span> Does it heal, restore, and enrich the world?</li>
        </ol>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="topic-landing__band" aria-labelledby="topic-flourishing-stakes">
    <div class="container topic-landing__split">
      <div>
        <p class="topic-landing__section-label">Why it matters</p>
        <h2 id="topic-flourishing-stakes">Technology is never just a tool problem.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="topic-landing__prose">
        <p>Every technical system carries a vision of what people are for, how communities should work, and what kind of future is worth building. The practical challenge is to make that vision explicit before capability outruns wisdom.</p>
        <p>CTA approaches technology through disciplined hope: pursue progress, resist domination, protect the vulnerable, and judge innovation by whether it expands life-giving possibility for more people.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="topic-landing__band topic-landing__band--ink" aria-labelledby="topic-flourishing-principles">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="topic-landing__section-label">Working principles</p>
      <h2 id="topic-flourishing-principles">What responsible progress requires</h2>
      <div class="topic-landing__principles">
        <article>
          <p class="topic-landing__number">01</p>
          <h3>Technology serving life</h3>
          <p>Progress should be evaluated by whether it cultivates, heals, protects, and empowers living communities.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <p class="topic-landing__number">02</p>
          <h3>Human dignity at the center</h3>
          <p>Efficiency, scale, and speed cannot replace the moral claim of persons and communities affected by a system.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <p class="topic-landing__number">03</p>
          <h3>Broad participation</h3>
          <p>Technological futures should be shaped by more than investors, engineers, and early adopters.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <p class="topic-landing__number">04</p>
          <h3>Accountable hope</h3>
          <p>Hope becomes credible when it accepts risk, listens to critique, and remains accountable to the people it claims to serve.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

